<br>
Having said that order is the opposite of chaos what constitutes order? Well good and evil are rules in a way, they are sets and standards that one must follow to stay good or evil. By having rules order is present.<br>
<br>
Now if evil is based in order and order is the opposite of chaos then how can behavior be both chaotic and evil at the same time, simply put it cant. That is why traditionally chaotic evil clasified people are completly insane. They are a walking contradiction.<br>
<br>
In order to be truly chaotic one must be willing to ignore completly and totally what is both good and evil. they must follow no rules, even the ones that they set for themselves. <br>
In addition to this anyone wanting chaos to rule is actually seeking order. Because it is actually a selfish attempt to apply the persons rules of &quot;chaos&quot; on others thus making order when those rules are followed.<br>
 <br>
Im sorry if this seems cryptic or hard to follow, i sometimes have trouble expressing the thoughts in my mind when they are as abstract as chaos.<br>
<br>
