<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> As the Sebilite finishes speaking, the white-haired Koada'Dal smiles -- or perhaps smirks; the magics around him cause the shadows to warp and dart as waves in an ocean -- and speaks. His voice is light and airy, but carries a darker, deeper undertone of command, brought out especially when he speaks in the tongue of the Iksar...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Your sense of duty is commendable, servitor of Thule. Your fear has made you strong, and while I do not venerate your 'god,' I have found his followers to be... most impressive adventurers. If I may, however, ask you a question, as my friend, a Crusader of Greenmist, has not yet reached your level of enlightenment and involvement in the politics of your Empire. Do the castes of your Empire reflect power and achievement, rather than politicking and birth? If they do, I suspect it would be natural and proper for you to dominate Norrath, as you would be bringing the order of a meritocracy to lands that are now, with few exceptions, ruled by the corrupt and the incompetent. Corruption, of course, takes many forms, but claiming one can lead the powerful without having power oneself is hypocrisy and the highest corruption of all. I suspect most adventurers here would agree,&quot; the Enchanter comments as his granite eyes scan the room, &quot;that the strong should lead. Strength is, after all, an objective measure, so long as one defines what strength is important for what position. The barbarian, for instance, if he is truly strong, would make an excellent warlord, while the Artkeepers would make masterful lords of the magical forces. Even those who practice the fine art of arbitration, such as myself, have a place once our strength in that is proven.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;On the other hand, if birth is key, your system is no less corrupt than others. If those not of your kind who accept the meritocracy cannot gain access to the positions to which they are most able, we once again have the weak leading the strong, which is a quick way to disrupt the carefully structured order. I would like to think more of your Empire, of course, as from what I have seen, it seems to be far superior to the conspiratorial kingdoms of Antonica, Odus, and Faydwer,&quot; he states, narrowing his eyes and sharply, bitterly, accenting the final word.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The magus lifts one brow slightly, awaiting a response, as the waitress fills his stein.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 593<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/4/02 12:16:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> &quot;Before an Iksar is hatched, the Hierophant's use their magic to determine the Iksar's natural abilities, and he is then assigned a caste based on where his talents would provide the most use. Who ones father is has no bareing on his caste or position. We have no desire to allow outsiders within our society, those not hatched Iksar are hatched flawed and weak, and have not been raised properly. We may accept Iksar who are hatched from beyond the Empire's borders who seek to redeem themselves and join us, but not other species. They are flawed, and allowing them in would be a mistake.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;We are strong, soft skin, Iksar are always assigned to the caste they are best suited for. Under the rare circumstance an Iksar shows he is truly gifted at a caste he was not assigned, his caste is changed. One can recieve training from other castes in their off time, if they so wish, although their skill will never match those assigned to that caste. Those who prove they are incompetent are killed, so there are few, if any, incompetent Iksar. We have politics, but they are few and nothing like yours.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The only exception to this is the Emperor, who is suceeded by one of his heirs. But even the Emperor's offspring belong to a caste themselves.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Does that answer your question?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 8/4/02 12:52:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/5/02 5:25:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The Koada'Dal rubs his chin, listening intently to the Sebilite's reply. He then takes a sip of his brew, and speaks.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;It does. Interesting, that. At least among your own kind, you have the right idea. However, I don't see why prudent alliances with those who share your point of view -- or, rather, at least some of your point of view -- is such a negative thing. It sounds almost as if your empire is falling to the same curse of bigotry and unreasoning hatred that's weakened the rest of Norrath. If I conspire to destroy your country, as the Teir'Dal are doing to the proud Ogres and the Fier'Dal, I can understand your hatred. However, when I work to establish a meritocracy similar to your caste system, and battle our mutual foes, I don't understand why, by birth, I am inherently at fault for the actions of the other Koada'Dal which, admittedly, are not necessarily wise,&quot; the magus states matter-of-factly, with a slight hint of detachment in his voice.<br>
<br>
After a brief pause, he continues. &quot;I also agree that your politics can't possibly be as bad as those on Antonica, Odus, and Faydwer. The clerics and paladins of Felwithe have a conspiracy to destroy the Keepers of the Art, for instance, and there's a secret war going on in the streets of Freeport. Cabilis is far more peaceful.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;In any event, I don't, of course, begrudge you your beliefs. I just happen to specialize in the fine art of arbitration, so I'm interested in knowing both sides and trying to draw everyone into a mutually beneficial agreement. Allying all adventurers of Norrath into a powerful organization to overthrow the false lords who claim rulership through divine right or appointed position, I think, would serve everyone's goals and establish a new age of order.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course, to do that,&quot; the magus smirks and winks, &quot;we'd need to get past the issue of birth determining value. I think even the advocates of chaos, like the Teir'Dal on the stage, would have a place as the armies of this new order. Giving people the ability to do what they want to do -- in his case, destroy everything -- is always advantageous, and at least in the cases of some, fear would be a powerful ally in controlling them. I can see the Sebilites acting as the commanders of a glorious military working in the service of Order.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A misty, wistful look crosses his eyes for a moment. He then takes another swig of his drink and turns back to the Sebilite.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A> at: 8/6/02 12:54:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 599<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 2:21:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> &quot;It is simple soft skin, our views do not include those who are not Iksar. It cannot be done.&quot;<br>
<br>
The shaman takes a big breath, looking at Illudin closely.<br>
<br>
&quot;You creatures are born flawed. You are not Iksar, you do not act or think like Iksar, you are inferior, and as such there would be problems if you were to live amongst us. The natural tendencies of you creatures are different from us,  you are different in ways we find revolting.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Also, everyone in our society has a clearly defined rank, according to their caste, and their position within their caste. Those who belong to no caste, and have no rank, our society simply does not have a method of accomodating. Who do they take orders from? What are they allowed and not allowed to do? Our society doesn't accomodate this. Visitors from outside have no place amongst us. Perhaps some system could be worked out if we truly desired for outsiders to be amongst us, but we do not. As I said, they are flawed.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;As long as there are multiple nations, races, and independent countries, they WILL fight, and they WILL war, and they WILL betray eachother. The only way this will ever stop is if there is only one nation, and one ruling goverment. We Iksar intend to become that nation. Once we rule, the petty wars and fights will cease. The only form of co-exsistance we will tolerate is if we can be assured we shall never, ever have to interact with those beyond our borders, and the chances of such a relationship developing are slim, and even if they did, someone would eventually break it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We all revere Cazic-Thule, and we won't tolerate the worship of false gods, nor shall we tolerate the worship of ones self. The ways of fear shall be the only path followed, and the only path allowed.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;We do not have any desire to be part of a joint army with lesser beings who will lie, betray, backstab, and run around doing their greedy little soft skin things and worshipping false gods. We do not wish to command troops we do not have anything but the utmost faith in, Iksar. Espicially not those wretched Tier Dal. Those things should be wiped off of Norrath permanently.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Some Iksar work with soft skins, yes. But just remember when the time comes and the Empire calls, we shall be enemies.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Does that answer your question, soft skin? Do you have any more?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 8/8/02 2:40:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugravesfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graves FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 11:08:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Time is soon.</span><hr size=1> Word reaches the catacombs.  Laughing, he puts down his mortal and pestal.  Scooping the last remenants of his latest mold onto a dry cloth, he folds it and places it in his traveling bag.<br>
<br>
A wink to the old hag in the corner, once a beautiful maiden of Qeynos, Graves grabs his scythe and starts for the secret panel.  As he is about to exit, he is guided by words of his mentor....<br>
<br>
&quot;Graves, be silent out there.  Time is on our side.  Spread the plague.  Let the fools fight with metal and their weak hearts.  In the end, there is only one side and our plague can't be stopped.&quot;<br>
<br>
Graves turned and nodded at his mentor.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I shall take note of your words wise one.  Arrogance is for the weak.  Challenging in battle eventually will kill the messenger.  We wait for the weaken victor to stand alone and then we shall reign all lands.  I shall use the shadows to our benefit and poison the fields, the water and the land as our creator wishes.&quot;<br>
<br>
Graves exits through the panel ...<br>
