<br>
&quot;hmm, so back to this old hat again? Well, as much as I love a good argument, we all know for any survival, order must prevail, even chaos is order in and of itself...&lt;snickers&gt; Everything happens from a simple cause and effect pattern, unless we are to expect intervention from a supreme deity, but those &quot;gods&quot; I fear, cannot interfere any longer as we have over powered even them...<br>
Which means cause and effect, a simple rule of order, rules all our lives, no matter how much one can try and escape it, it follows you. &lt;mutters a bit under his breathe&gt; Order is a path for the wise, not because we wish to follow it, but because we know that it is the only true path...<br>
&lt;closing his eyes and relapsing into a long drawn out memory&gt; <br>
You know, I would prefer being ignorant, since ignorance is bliss, and following chaos. Even those who say they are chaotic are doing so from a cause, whether its because they are in search of a money &lt;chuckles&gt; which could have infinite causes, to sheer lust for destruction which could stem from a disgruntled childhood to a unfortunate accident in the past....&lt;sighs heavily, and takes a long drink from the pitcher&gt; Either way, I know you will continue believing your following you non-existant path, and more power to you, but order is the only path, and cannot be deviated from, sad as it is...&lt;soon becomes overtaken by sudden grief, and leaves in search of the bottom of the pitcher or 10&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zatranik>Zatranik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/2/02 4:52:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Chaos</span><hr size=1>   Suddenly, a hole breaks in the ceiling and a figure falls through. He tries throwing the fallen pieces back into their hole, which just makes them fall back down and hit his head.<br>
